CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 19, 1960, pg. A13 reads: "Brotherhood Festival Participants - To Take Part In Festival - Among the many groups taking part in national Council of Negro Women's Brotherhood Food Festival on March 26 at the Hotel Penn-Sheraton will be Mrs. Frances Primas (seated front) and Mrs. Ruth Amend, representing the Delta Patronesses Board and Allegheny County Council of Church Women, respectively. Standing: Mmes. Lucille Ellett, Daughter Elks; Daisy Pannill, Wesley Center Church School; Geraldine Graves, Judy Lee Jewels; Eva Thomas, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority; Helen Thompson, Urban League; Ann H. Proudfoot, Pennsylvania Licensed Practical Nurses; Jennie Dobbins, Lucy Stone Civic League; Mary Ellen Pennywell, UNCF and Fashionettes.  -Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Brotherhood Festival participants, from left, seated: Frances Primas and Ruth Amend; standing: Lucille Ellett, Daisy Pannill, Geraldine Graves, Judy Lee Jewels; Eva Thomas, Helen Thompson, Ann H. Proudfoot, Jennie Dobbins, and Mary Ellen Pennywell, posed in interior with floral curtains and light colored venetian blinds
